EGPA combined GWAS summary statistics

lyons_egpa.Rd

Summary data from GWAS study of EGPA of 534 cases and 6,688 controls

data(lyons_egpa)

Format

A data.table object of odds ratios, beta standard errors and p values.

References

Lyons et al. Nat Commun 10, 5120 (2019) doi:10.1038/s41467-019-12515-9 (DOI)

Examples

data(lyons_egpa)
head(lyons_egpa)
#>    CHR      BP a1 a2        or        seb p.value
#> 1:   1 1239953  A  G 0.9540296 0.13277346    0.52
#> 2:   1 1744812  A  G 1.1077122 0.21219596    0.52
#> 3:   1 2513216  C  T 1.0773496 0.05533328    0.59
#> 4:   1 2526746  G  A 0.9825316 0.05751922    0.86
#> 5:   1 2709164  C  A 1.0052302 0.05851229    0.74
#> 6:   1 4698559  C  T 0.9576941 0.07558322    0.44
